\section{Introduction}

Principia softwarica is a set of books explaining how things work in a
computer by describing with full details all the concrete code of all
the essential software running on a typical machine. 
%
Among those essential software are the kernel, the shell, the 
windowing system, the compiler, the debugger, etc.
They are mostly all \co{meta} programs: 
programs dealing with other programs (a.k.a system software).
For instance the kernel is a program that {\em manages} other programs,
the compiler is a program that {\em generates} other programs.

